 1. Preprocessing (src/utils/preprocessing.py)
                                                                                           
  What it does                                                                           

  Raw book text goes through these steps before indexing:

  1. Boilerplate removal — Project Gutenberg wraps every book with legal headers/footers
  between *** START OF... *** and *** END OF... *** markers. These are stripped so only the
   actual book content is indexed. If markers aren't found, the first 100 lines are skipped
   (they're typically the header).
  2. Unicode normalisation (NFC) — Characters like ö in "Dornröschen" can be stored in
  multiple ways in Unicode. NFC normalisation collapses them into a single consistent form
  so the query "Dornröschen" matches the indexed form.
  3. Lowercasing — "Hamlet" and "hamlet" should match the same term.
  4. Tokenisation (NLTK word_tokenize) — Splits text into tokens, handling punctuation,
  contractions, etc. better than a simple split().
  5. Punctuation removal — Keeps only tokens that contain at least one word character (\w),
   discarding pure punctuation tokens.
  6. Stopword removal (title/author only) — Common words like "the", "of", "and" are
  removed when indexing title and author fields. This makes structured field searches
  cleaner. Crucially, stopwords are NOT removed from body text — they are kept because:
    - Phrase search needs them (e.g. "to be or not to be")
    - Positional information is preserved for all tokens

  Two preprocessing modes

  ┌────────────────────┬────────────────────────┬───────────────────┐
  │       Method       │        Used for        │ Stopwords removed │
  ├────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
  │ preprocess_body()  │ Indexing book text     │ No                │
  ├────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
  │ preprocess_field() │ Indexing title, author │ Yes               │
  └────────────────────┴────────────────────────┴───────────────────┘

